21/03/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US Embassy in Skopje was closed Thursday (20 March) after the government received warning of a possible attack. "The Department of State has received credible information that there are persons intent on attacking Americans and US facilities in the region, including Macedonia, in response to the initiation of armed conflict with Iraq," the embassy said in a statement. Macedonian and US officials are working together to address the threat. The State Department announced that 12 other missions were also closed. (AP, AFP - 20/03/03)
